  "text": "The plugin signature verification system in grafana/grafana spans three concerns:\n\n1. **Manifest signing & parsing** (`pkg/plugins/manager/signature/manifest.go`): The `Signature` struct implements `SignatureCalculator`. It reads `MANIFEST.txt` (PGP clearsigned JSON), decodes it, validates required fields, verifies the PGP signature against public keys retrieved via `KeyRetriever`, and then checks file hashes, version/ID matching, and root URL constraints. The static public key is embedded in `statickey/static_retriever.go`; dynamic keys are fetched from grafana.com API via `keyretriever/dynamic/dynamic_retriever.go`, with a coordinator in `keyretriever/retriever.go`.\n\n2. **Signature validation on load** (`pkg/plugins/manager/signature/signature.go` + `pkg/plugins/manager/pipeline/validation/steps.go`): The `Validation` struct implements signature validation as a pipeline step. During bootstrap (`bootstrap/steps.go`), `DefaultConstructor.Construct` calls `Calculate` to compute signature status. During validation, `PluginSignatureValidator` calls `ValidateSignature` which checks the computed status and rejects unsigned/invalid/modified plugins.\n\n3. **Unsigned plugin allowlist** (`pkg/plugins/manager/signature/authorizer.go` + `pkg/plugins/config/config.go`): `UnsignedPluginAuthorizer` implements `PluginLoaderAuthorizer`. Its `CanLoadPlugin` method checks `PluginsAllowUnsigned` (a list of plugin IDs) and `DevMode` from `PluginManagementCfg`. Type definitions for `SignatureStatus`, `SignatureType`, and `Signature` live in `pkg/plugins/models.go`; interfaces (`SignatureCalculator`, `KeyRetriever`, `PluginLoaderAuthorizer`) are in `pkg/plugins/ifaces.go`.",
